## Statement of Purpose

The laws of most jurisdictions throughout the world automatically confer exclusive Copyright and Related Rights (defined below) upon the creator and subsequent owner(s) (each and all, an "owner") of an original work of authorship and/or a database (each, a "Work").

Certain owners wish to permanently abandon those exclusive Rights, and thus to dedicate such Work(s) to the public domain. The intent of this Legal Code is to facilitate the widespread use of Works by authors, artists, scientists, educators, and other creators, as well as archivists, librarians, researchers, and organizations, such as digital archives and repositories ("Organizations").

This dedication is designed to provide a universal, non-exclusive, royalty-free, perpetual license to use the Work for any and all purposes, including commercial and non-commercial purposes, throughout the world and in any jurisdiction.

